import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='mean delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', label='median delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['distance']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data.values, vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, labels=['Distance'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.axvline(x=data.mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data.mean()[0]:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by=['counts'], ascending=False)
    data = data.head(10)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination'], data['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Route')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('Which airports have the most flights?')
    ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay')
    ax.axvline(x=data['distance'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median Distance')
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['hour'] = data['date'].dt.hour
    flights_by_hour = data.groupby('hour').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    plt.plot(flights_by_hour['hour'], flights_by_hour['counts'], color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=flights_by_hour['hour'].iloc[flights_by_hour['counts'].idxmax()], color='red', label='Busiest hour: {:.2f}'.format(flights_by_hour['hour'].iloc[flights_by_hour['counts'].idxmax()]))
    plt.xlabel('Hour of the day')
    plt.ylabel('Number of flights')
    plt.title('What is the busiest time of day for flights?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
